==English==
===Pronunciation===
IPA: /gɪmp/

===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
{{en-noun-reg|gimp}}
#A narrow ornamental fabric of silk, woolen, or cotton, often with a metallic wire, or sometimes a coarse cord, running through it; -- used as trimming for dresses, furniture, etc.
#A limp or a limping gait.
#A person who is lame due to a crippling of the legs or feet.
#A crippled leg.
#(''Commonwealth English slang'') A contemptible and dull person with very poor social skills [derogatory].
#[[BDSM]]: A sexual submissive, almost always male, dressed generally in a black leather suit.

===Verb===
[[Category:English verbs]]
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|gimp||}}
#To notch; to indent; to jag.
#To limp; to hobble.

===Adjective===
[[Category:English adjectives]]
'''gimp'''
#Smart; spruce; trim; nice.

